stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Open : BufferedInputStream BufferedInputStream([InputStream in])
    [*] --> Open : BufferedInputStream BufferedInputStream([InputStream in], [int size])

    Open --> Open : int read()
    Open --> Open : int read([byte[] b], [int off], [int len])
    Open --> Open : long skip([long n])
    Open --> Open : int available()
    Open --> Open : boolean markSupported()
    Open --> Marked : void mark([int readlimit])
    Open --> Closed : void close()

    Marked --> Marked : int read()
    Marked --> Marked : int read([byte[] b], [int off], [int len])
    Marked --> Marked : long skip([long n])
    Marked --> Marked : int available()
    Marked --> Marked : boolean markSupported()
    Marked --> Marked : void mark([int readlimit])
    Marked --> Marked : void reset()
    Marked --> Closed : void close()

    Closed --> Closed : void close()
    Closed --> [*]

    note right of Open
        No mark set. reset() is forbidden.
        mark() transitions to Marked state.
    end note

    note right of Marked
        Mark position is set. reset() is permitted.
        mark() can be called again to update mark position.
    end note

    note right of Closed
        Terminal state. close() is idempotent.
        read(), skip(), available(), reset() throw IOException.
    end note
